        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The Trip Computer Distance to Empty function calculates an estimate of the number of miles or kilometres, which can be travelled on the remaining volume of fuel in the tank. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                12,
                53,
                962,
                97
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "After battery connection “Distance to Empty” uses a starting value for the “Instantaneous Fuel Consumption” (determined by diagnostic command, default 4.70l/100km, equivalent to 50 mpg uk/60 mpg us). "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                12,
                101,
                976,
                145
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The calculation will become more accurate over time, such that “Distance to Empty” will be calculated based on the riding style and economy of the individual rider. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                12,
                149,
                976,
                193
            ]
        },
